                <head>79. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At the 371st meeting of the National Security Council on July 3, <persName
                        corresp="#p_DAW1">Allen W. Dulles</persName> briefly commented on the
                    situation in Cuba. According to the memorandum of discussion, <persName
                        corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName> expressed his view that the news from
                    Cuba was “a good deal better, and that the Americans <pb facs="0158" n="126"
                        xml:id="pg_126"/> captured by the rebel forces would be gradually freed in
                    groups until all had been released.” (Eisenhower Library, Whitman File, <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Records)</p>
            </div>
